        <p rend="right"><date n="1947-11-02">November 2, 1947</date></p>

        <p><emph n="salutation">Dear Mr. <persName key="73655" role="rec"
          >Schocken</persName></emph>:</p>

        <p>Only yesterday did I learn from " <orgName key="74649">Aufbau</orgName>" that you have
          celebrated <date n="1947-10-30">your seventieth anniversary last week</date>.
          So I am unfortunately coming too late with my congratulations. But they are nevertheless
          sincere and affectionate. I have always looked up to you, admiring the scope of your
          interests and your magnificent readiness to translate ideas into actions. And it is a
          profoundly comforting thought that you are now carrying on with undiminished strength, in
          a tireless effort to spread the best of Jewish culture and heart. I personally owe much to
          what you have done and so do innumerable others. And I also wish to tell you on this
          occasion that, whenever I had the opportunity of talking with you, I felt deeply impressed
          and elated by the power and radiance of your personality. These rare conversations belong
          among my most treasured memories.</p>

        <p rend="center"><emph n="salute">Many happy returns. And all my good wishes</emph>.</p>

        <p rend="center"><emph n="salute">Sincerely yours</emph>,</p>

        <p rend="center"><persName role="aut" key="7721">Siegfried Kracauer</persName></p>

